.TH OPTIMIZE 1 "July 2026" "2.0.0" "optimize manual"
.SH NAME
optimize \- rebuild Debian/Ubuntu packages with hardware-aware optimization
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B optimize
[\fB-p\fR|\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB-c\fR|\fB--cflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR]
[\fB-x\fR|\fB--cxxflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR]
[\fB-j\fR|\fB--jobs\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB-o\fR|\fB--output-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
.I package-name
.PP
.B optimize
\fB--kernel\fR
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B optimize
[\fB-h\fR|\fB--help\fR]
.PP
.B optimize
[\fB-V\fR|\fB-v\fR|\fB--version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B optimize
rebuilds official Debian/Ubuntu source packages using the standard
\fBsbuild\fR and \fBdebian/rules\fR flow. It preserves the distribution
packaging process and changes only controlled build parameters.
.PP
The default profile is \fBnative-safe\fR, which preserves the optimization
level chosen by the distribution and appends native CPU targeting flags when
supported. More aggressive optimization is available through explicit profiles.
.SH PROFILES
.TP
\fBvendor\fR
Use distribution flags unchanged.
.TP
\fBnative-safe\fR
Preserve the distribution optimization level and append native CPU targeting.
This is the default.
.TP
\fBnative-aggressive\fR
Append \fB-O3\fR plus native CPU targeting.
.TP
\fBadaptive\fR
Try \fBnative-aggressive\fR, then \fBnative-safe\fR, then \fBvendor\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-p\fR, \fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Select the build profile.
.TP
\fB-c\fR, \fB--cflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR
Set custom \fBDEB_CFLAGS_APPEND\fR. This selects the \fBcustom\fR profile.
.TP
\fB-x\fR, \fB--cxxflags\fR \fIFLAGS\fR
Set custom \fBDEB_CXXFLAGS_APPEND\fR.
.TP
\fB-j\fR, \fB--jobs\fR \fIN\fR
Specify the number of parallel build jobs.
.TP
\fB-o\fR, \fB--output-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR
Set the output directory. Defaults to \fB./optimize-output\fR.
.TP
\fB--suite\fR \fICODENAME\fR
Override the detected distribution suite.
.TP
\fB--chroot-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Select \fBauto\fR, \fBunshare\fR, or \fBschroot\fR.
.TP
\fB--no-check\fR
Disable package tests explicitly.
.TP
\fB--install\fR
Install generated packages using \fBapt-get install\fR.
.TP
\fB-k\fR, \fB--kernel\fR
Run the experimental tailored kernel build path. If native CPU compiler flags
are unavailable, this mode continues with \fB-O2\fR and still applies the
hardware-aware configuration steps. Signed kernel wrapper source packages are
normalized to the buildable unsigned kernel source package.
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB-v\fR, \fB--version\fR
Show version information and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBmanifest.yaml\fR
Written in the output record directory with source, profile, flags, tests,
artifacts, and checksums.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B optimize
uses a temporary \fBSBUILD_CONFIG\fR file for each build attempt. It does not
modify \fB~/.sbuildrc\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apt-get (8),
.BR dpkg-buildflags (1),
.BR sbuild (1),
.BR schroot (1)
